casebody.data:
The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v Al Armstrong, Appellant.

—Appeal by defendant from a judgment of the County Court, Westchester County (Nastasi, J.), rendered April 19, 1983, convicting him of criminal possession of stolen property in the first degree, upon his plea of guilty, and imposing sentence.

Judgment affirmed.

We have reviewed the record and agree with defendant’s assigned counsel that there are no meritorious issues that could be raised on appeal. Counsel’s application for leave to withdraw as counsel is granted (see, Anders v California, 386 US 738; People v Paige, 54 AD2d 631; cf. People v Gonzalez, 47 NY2d 606). Mollen, P. J., Gibbons, Brown, Niehoff and Eiber, JJ., concur.
